 159:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        By default, after the HAL_I2S_Init() and when the state is HAL_I2S_STATE_RESET
 160:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 161:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        examples HAL_I2S_MasterTxCpltCallback(), HAL_I2S_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 162:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 163:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_I2S_Init()/ HAL_I2S_DeInit() only when
 164:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 165:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_I2S_Init()/ HAL_I2S_DeInit()
 166:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state
 167:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c **** 
 168:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        [..]
 169:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_I2S_STATE_READY state only.
 170:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 171:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        in HAL_I2S_STATE_READY or HAL_I2S_STATE_RESET state,
 172:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 173:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 174:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        using HAL_I2S_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_I2S_DeInit()
 175:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        or HAL_I2S_Init() function.
 176:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c **** 
 177:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        [..]
 178:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        When the compilation define USE_HAL_I2S_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 179:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 180:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****        and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
 181:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c **** 
 182:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s.c ****   @endverbatim
